input: The cow is not cold. The cow does not see the lion. The cow visits the lion. The dog likes the cow. The dog sees the squirrel. The dog visits the lion. The lion is round. universe u

constant obj : Type u

constant Cow : obj
constant Dog : obj
constant Lion : obj
constant Squirrel : obj

constant Cold : obj → Prop
constant Sees : obj → obj → Prop
constant Visits : obj → obj → Prop
constant Likes : obj → obj → Prop
constant Round : obj → Prop
constant Young : obj → Prop

axiom T1 : ¬ Cold Cow
axiom T2 : ¬ Sees Cow Lion
axiom T3 : Visits Cow Lion
axiom T4 : Likes Dog Cow
axiom T5 : Sees Dog Squirrel
axiom T6 : Visits Dog Lion
axiom T7 : Round Lion
axiom T8 : Sees Lion Cow
axiom T9 : Sees Lion Dog
axiom T10 : Visits Squirrel Lion

axiom R1 : Likes Dog Lion ∧ Likes Lion Squirrel → Likes Dog Squirrel
axiom R2 : ∀ x : obj, Likes x Cow ∧ Likes Cow Dog → Visits x Squirrel
axiom R3 : ∀ x : obj, Visits Dog Squirrel → Young x
axiom R4 : ∀ x : obj, Young x → Visits x Dog
axiom R5 : ∀ x : obj, Sees x Cow → ¬ Sees Cow Dog
axiom R6 : ∀ x : obj, Likes x Dog ∧ ¬ Cold x → Likes x Squirrel
axiom R7 : ∀ x : obj, Visits x Lion → Likes x Dog
axiom R8 : ∀ x : obj, Visits x Dog ∧ Likes Dog Cow → Round Dog
axiom R9 : ∀ x : obj, Visits x Lion ∧ ¬ Sees x Dog → Visits x Cow

theorem dog_is_round : Round Dog :=
begin
  apply R8,
  split,
  apply R4,
  apply R3 Dog,
  exact T6,
  exact T4,
end

-- The answer is True
